- F-008: Withdraw and emergency-withdraw can silently burn a user's claim when token transfers return false (Medium, high)
- F-010: Non-stable pool snapshots trust raw contract balances instead of tracked user stake (Medium, high)
- F-011: Permissionless interest sweeps can front-run stablecoin withdrawals and worsen liquidity shortfalls (Medium, low)
- F-012: Anyone can overwrite an already-initialized epoch-0 pool snapshot (Medium, high)
- F-013: Permissionless `getInterest()` can confiscate unrelated stablecoins held by the contract (Medium, high)
- F-014: Unexpected cToken transfers are misclassified as protocol yield and can be swept to the team (Medium, high)

